{ The point of trading those knights on d4 is that White opens up the path for the f-pawn, and g4-f4 ideas become a thing now.   Note that  8...Nxe5?  is bad because of  9.Bb5+  Nd7  10.Nxf5  exf5  11.Qxd5  and White has regained the pawn with Black's king dangerously stuck in the center. }
8... Nge7 { This is the better way, but not everyone is aware of that. } 9. Bb5
{ This is an entirely new idea, with some very nasty tactical points. Luckily for us, L'Ami's LTR doesn't mention it, so his followers will have to figure it out on their own for now. }
9... a6 { Forcing the trade gives us a pleasant advantage. } 10. Bxc6+ Nxc6 11.
Nxf5 exf5 12. Qd3 g6 13. Nd2 Bg7 14. Nf3 O-O 15. Bf4
{ White is better here, with the d5-pawn being so weak and our pieces fully mobilized around our e5-pawn. }
