Na3
{ A couple of old correspondence games saw White going  10.Bg5  , which can lead to a lot of trades after  10...a6  or  10...h6  with only a symbolic advantage for White in the end. This move is an attempt to confuse Black and just go for the lead in the development. }
10... a6 11. Bxc6+ bxc6
