{ Of course this is possible, but Black is better off including  9...Rc8  10.Bb2  before going for ...Nf5. }
10. Bxf5
{ It's not a bad moment to take. Also very interesting is  10.Re1!?  intending  10...Be7  11.c4!?  similar to the 8...Nf5 line. }
10... exf5 11. cxd4 Be7 12. Nc3 Be6 13. Qd3
{ This is just one of White's possible setups, but it's a very reasonable one. Generally, we want to follow up with Bd2 and Na4 ideas. }
13... h6 14. Bd2
{ And next we will send the knight via a4 towards c5. Another route is Ne2-Nf4. }
