{ The most useful move of all the waiting ones, not rushing with development of the kingside just yet, since  9...Nf5  allows  10.Bxf5  and @@StartFEN@@r3kb1r/pp1b1ppp/1qn1p2n/3pP3/1P1p4/P1PB1N2/5PPP/RNBQ1RK1 b kq b3 0 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Be7  10.Bxh6  .   Besides waiting, the move  9...Rc8  also creates some clever concrete ideas. For example,  10.Re1  is now met with  10...dxc3  11.Nxc3  Ng4!  12.Ra2  Ncxe5!  or  12...Nxb4!  ,  when the knight on c3 hangs. }
