{ The most common move, but now we get a lot of tempi on the Black queen. } 8.
b4 { Kicking the queen back to b6. } 8... Qb6 9. c4
{ Opening the a1-h8 diagonal, making sure our e5-pawn is going to be well guarded by the bishop from b2, but also just adding pressure on the center. }
9... dxc4 10. Nbd2 { A strong move, the knight will recapture the pawn. } *

