{ If instead Black goes for the modest  12...Be7  we can go for the Nbd2 c4 plan or the more dynamic  13.c4!?  dxc4  14.Be4!  intending to eventually pick up the c4-pawn. }
13. Bb5 { Black has to deal with Qxd5 here. That's why we started with Re1. } *

