{ Both myself and Caruana have played the automatic  8.Nc2  here, but in this particular position Bxa3 is not a big threat since Black just loses too much time on all the movements of the g6-knight. The simple idea of h5! is just really hard to meet. }
8... cxd4 9. cxd4 Bb4+
{ This is wrong, as we really don't mind going Kf1 for free. } 10. Kf1
{ We are happy here, as out king is perfectly safe on f1 and the rook will be active on the h-file, potentially swing Rh3-Rg3 in some lines. }
