6... cxd4 { The right way to try and trade the light-squared bishops. } 7. cxd4
Bb5
{ Here taking on b5 is less attractive, since we will be unable to get to the b-pawn as it will move to b4 and be well guarded by the black pieces. Instead, I propose to play in a simple manner. }
8. Nc3 { The knight is going to be excellently placed on e2. } 8... Bxe2 9.
Nxe2
{ The knight is excellent on e2, from where it can hop onwards to the kingside. We have a familiar pawn structure and good kingside potential.  9...Bb4+  is always met with  10.Kf1!  in these types of positions. }
