9. Ngf3 c4
{ This move can be somewhat bothersome, since now our move a3 doesn't look very useful, as b3 can sometimes be met with cxb3 when we can't recapture axb3. }
10. O-O
{ White has potential here as well, with a well timed kingside pawnstorm perhaps. These positions are just very murky and double edged. }
