{ The only square, as  15...Qxa2?  gets the queen trapped after  16.Ra1  and  15...Qb6?  allows  16.c4!  blasting the position open. }
16. Rc2
{ A tricky quiet move, preparing Nb3. The immediate  16.Nb3  would be met with  16...Na5! }
16... Be7
{ A mistake, but it is hard to find a move more natural than this one. } 17.
Nb3
{ The point is that  17...Na5  is now met with  18.Nbc5!  and the threat of Bc1 is deadly. }
17... Nxe3
{ This is just positionally bad. Without the knight on f5 and with the open f-file, Black will get smashed on the kingside. }
18. fxe3 O-O 19. Qg4
{ The attack will develop itself with ideas like Nf4-Nh5 and Raf2. } *

