{ What could be more natural. } 15. Bh5
{ An unusual idea. Suddenly Black has to deal with some f4-f5 threats. } 15...
c5 { Black needs counterplay and Black needs it quickly. } 16. Re1
{ A very challenging sequence, but  16.dxc5  Bxc5  17.Qg3  is also a way to put the pressure on. }
16... Bd7 { The best square for the bishop. } 17. Qf3
{ Every unexpected move is like a punch. Suddenly Black has to deal with the prospect of a tricky endgame. }
17... cxd4 { This is logical, but we have a strong sequence in reply. } 18.
Qxf7+ Kxf7 19. Nxg6 hxg6 20. Bf3 Be6
{ So far all the moves were natural and easy, but now it's time for a strong one. }
21. Na3
{ The knight is very effective here and Black is welcome to give up the bishop pair. }
21... Bxa3
{ Getting rid of the knight is the normal way to try and get rid of the problems, but they do remain. }
22. bxa3 Nc6 23. Rad1
{ It's hard to suggest a way for Black to untangle and get rid of the pressure or further simplify. We have plenty of useful moves at our disposal, such as h4, Rd2 at a certain moment we can also think of regrouping our bishops. }
