9... Ne7 { The obvious reply. } 10. dxc5
{ A standard way to get things moving, dxc5 followed by Nd4. } 10... Nxc5 11.
Nd4
{ Some relatively old correspondence games went  11.Nb3  first, but this move order seems smarter. }
11... Bg6 { This is actually more solid, avoiding any Bh5 ideas. } 12. N2b3
{ Transposing to the old correspondence games looks like a good idea, though  12.b4!?  is also very tempting. }
12... Nd7 13. cxd5 Nxd5 14. f4
{ The threat of f5 proved too strong here and White scored two out of two in the old correspondence games. That seems a little exaggerated, but White is indeed for choice. }
