8. Nf3 Bd6 9. Bb5 { This is a good way to get Black onto the defensive. } 9...
Nd7 10. g3 { Simply supporting the f4-pawn. } 10... a6
{ Black allows us to ruin his pawn structure, but it is hard for him to develop otherwise. }
