6. Ngxe2 Qa5
{ This is the way GM Shimanov plays and while it's better than the direct Qh5, it's still quite terrible. }
7. b4 { Castling first is strong as well, but this b4 idea is a good one. }
7... Qh5
{ Now Black hopes to exploit our weakend queenside, but what will get exploited instead is the misplaced queen on h5 and Black's lack of development. }
8. Qd3
{ A very creative and a powerful idea. The queen is going to be incredibly nasty on g3. }
8... e6 9. Qg3
{ Hitting c7 suddenly, but also keeping an eye on g7, not letting the f8 bishop develop. }
9... Na6 { The only way to defend the c7-pawn. } 10. a3
{ Now the a6-knight is offside. } 10... Qg6 11. Qf3
{ We don't trade into an endgame of course, as we have the better development and a much safer king long term. }
11... O-O-O 12. O-O
{ Black is looking very clumsy on the queenside and we will have a free attack after Bf4 and ideas like Nb5. }
