11... Rd8 { Black has to play some daring chess to keep the fight alive. } 12.
Qg3 { Black is cramped, so he has to go for the pawn and not look back. } 12...
Qxd4 13. Nxd7 Qxd7 14. Rhe1
{ White has some long-term compensation here, as Black's king is stuck in the center. I will continue the line for the greedy people out there. }
14... Rg8 15. Bg5 Bd6 16. Qe3 Qc7 17. Qxa7
{ There were alternatives, but I know a lot of people won't calm down until they have regained the sacrificed pawn, so the last few moves are dedicated to them. Now White is better for free. The black king is still stuck in the center. }
