{ This is extremely rare, because it is essentially Black fighting for equality in a sad symmetrical endgame, which goes fully against the philosophy of the players who play the Pirc or the Modern. Still, it is the top choice of the best engines and objectively gives Black the best shot at equalizing the position. }
7. dxe5
{ We are happy to trade down into a slightly better endgame. Pirc players are not known to be great endgame specialists, as far as I know. }
7... dxe5 8. Nxe5
{ Trading the central pawns is fine for us too, especially since we gain some tempi and activate our pieces. }
8... Nxe4 { Black has this trick to restore the material balance. } 9. Nxe4
Qxd1 10. Rxd1
{ It's also possible to play the elegant  10.Bxd1!?  Bxe5  11.Re1  and later activate the d1-bishop by opening the d1-a4 diagonal with c3! White is slightly better there as well. }
10... Bxe5 11. c3
{ Erecting a block of pawns in front of the e5 bishop that now feels powerless. We have the more active pieces here and a more harmonious development, with the bishops ready to be employed on the diagonals. }
11... Nd7
{ A reasonable developing move. I just want to show a pretty sample line. There are many options along the way, of course, but this is just for demonstration purposes. }
12. Bg5 { The bishop is guarding some important squares. } 12... Kg7
{ Black is preparing Nf6. } 13. Be3
{ Suddenly the e5-bishop is short of squares. A very clever idea. } 13... Re8
14. Bb5
{ Very subtle play all around. Now we provoke a weakness of the d6-square. }
14... c6 15. Bc4
{ Any retreat is good at this point. We can and should allow the Bxh2+ cheapo. }
15... Bxh2+
{ Black wins a pawn, but the dark squares are going to be left unattended. }
16. Kxh2 Rxe4 17. Bd4+ { Check and we also prepare the e-file for a trade. }
17... Kf8 18. f3 { Getting an extra tempo in. } 18... Re8 19. Re1
{ Trading Black's only active piece. Our bishop pair is mighty and Black has to be very inventive here, to develop his queenside and survive this endgame, despite being up a pawn. }
