[Black "Pirc with 6...e6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6
{ The Pirc is a major opening, known for being somewhat dubious but at the same time perhaps the most fighting of all the weapons Black has at his disposal against 1. e4. Black gives up the fight for the center for now, thus avoiding complications and any direct clashes, postponing the fight for a murky middlegame.Indeed, if you outclass your opponent by a ton of rating points or if your opponent has no clue about what he is supposed to do, the Pirc @@StartBracket@@or the Modern defense for that matter, which is another move order to get to very similar positions@@EndBracket@@ is an excellent choice. In case of our opponents, however, they are going to be disappointed, as we have prepared a cold shower for them in this chapter. }
