6... a6
{ Looking at the games, I would say this is perhaps the most topical move at the highest level. Black's idea is to include  6...a6  7.a4  and then after  7...Nc6  8.d5  he will have two extra squares to move the knight to: b4 and a7. A clever thought, but White is still better. }
7. a4
{ We 'fall' for it and play the most natural move. Space on the queenside may start to matter at some point. }
7... b6
