9... Bb4
{ This is kind of disturbing if you don't know how to deal with it, but once you do, it's not great for Black. }
10. Be2
{ It would be a mistake to lose time and force the trade on c3 with a3. } 10...
Na5
{ Black is trying to be very annoying, but we can just defend everything. The same response comes after  10...O-O  11.O-O  Na5  , as the two move orders are likely to transpose to each other. }
11. c5 { The pawn has to protect itself. } 11... Nd5
{ There was nothing better.  11...Nac4  loses a piece to  12.Bg5  or  12.Bc1  , while @@StartFEN@@r2qk2r/ppp2ppp/1n2p3/n1P1Pb2/1b1P4/2N1BN2/PP2B1PP/R2QK2R b KQkq - 0 11@@EndFEN@@  11...Nbc4  is bad because of  12.Qa4+  c6  13.Bd2!  Nxd2  14.Qxb4  when the a5 knight is completely out of play. }
12. Bd2
{ Everything is guarded and we have nicely gained space in the meantime. White is much better here, with easy moves to follow. }
