[Result "*"]

1. e4 Nc6
{ This system really doesn't make all too much sense against us, as we are fine with all the transpositions that can eventually arise. }
2. Nf3
{ There is no need to get provoked. Also,  2.d4  d5  is actually not such a bad system for Black.   After  2.Nf3  if Black goes  2...e5  we can play our Italian @@StartBracket@@or a Spanish or Scotch if that's what you prefer@@EndBracket@@ and so in this chapter we should look at other options. }
2... d6
{ This move order makes a lot of sense against people who play systems without Nf3 against the Pirc, but against the Pirc we are playing the Nf3 Be2 system, so we don't care that the knight came out so early to c6. }
3. d4 Bg4
{ I faced this a lot in simuls where the players are just making their first chess steps. It's pretty terrible. }
4. d5 Ne5 5. Nxe5
{ This is a thematic trick. At the end of the line Black is in bad shape. }
5... Bxd1 6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 Qa5+
{ 7...a6  is the only other move, but then  8.c7+  gives us a winning endgame. }
8. Nc3 a6 9. b4
{ This is the clincher. Now after  9...Qxb4  10.cxb7+  axb5  the queen no longer defends the a8-rook and we mate with  11.bxa8=Q  . }
